'''Canlan Ice Sports Etobicoke''' is a four-pad hockey facility located at [[Ontario Highway 409]] and [[Martin Grove Road]] in [[Toronto]], [[Ontario]], [[Canada]]. The arena is owned and operated by Canlan Ice Sports Corporation, of [[Burnaby]], [[British Columbia]]. Canlan Ice Sports Corporation is a publicly traded company on the Toronto Stock Exchange with the call letters ICE.

The arena is home to The Toronto Marlboros Minor Hockey Organization, a member of the [[Greater Toronto Hockey League]] (GTHL).<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.torontomarlboros.com/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=58&Itemid=96 |title= Arena Locations|publisher= Toronto Marlboros Hockey Club|accessdate= 2010-07-04}}</ref>

The facility was a Gold Award winner of the 2007 [[Toronto Sun]] Readers' Choice Award in the category of the Recreational Hockey Arena.<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.icesports.com/etobicoke/about-us.aspx |title= About Us|publisher= Canlan Ice Sports Etobicoke|accessdate= 2010-07-04}}</ref>

